(20:25) Savu tells you 'I always set [Parry] to either 0 or 51 (the opposite maximums). At zero, parry is not on at all and my offensive power is at maximum. At 51, I am on defensive mode and my defenses are at max (I parry, and with riposte skill trained, some of the parries result in a low power counterattack which compensates the loss of damage due to parrying a bit). Of course it's best to try it yourself, but I've found this strategy working the best for me.'
(20:28) Savu tells you 'For example if I am in a situation where I am getting a lot of damage from hits, parry can help you get that critical attack skill in just in time before having to bail out. Or if there are multiple opponents, I set my target at one opponent at a time with my parry at 51 and use skill only at that one target. That way my offensive power is focused on one single target at a time and my parry protects me a bit from the others while I take out one by one.'

